comment.en:
A rehearsal event.
        Takes as agent the performer as well as a musicians group.

comment.undefined: A tour event. A tour comprises various performances.

comment.en: A sound engineer involved in sound engineering activities (e.g., mixing) during live music events (e.g., performances), either a human or a software agent.

comment.undefined: A chamber ensemble is a small group of musicians performing classical music. It usually features one player per part, without a conductor. Groups can range from duos to octets or more.

comment.en:
A jam session event.
        Takes as agent a musicians group.
An actual human being involved in a musical activity (e.g., composition, performance)
A software agent capable of performing a musical activity (e.g., composition via computational creativity techniques)

comment.undefined: A band is a group of musicians who play instruments together. Bands can perform various music styles, such as rock, jazz, or pop. They may perform with or without vocals.
A spacious, multi-purpose indoor venue for concerts, sports, and large events. It can host thousands of people with stage and lighting setups. Commonly used for pop, rock, and touring performances.
An actual human being involved in a performance activity.
An actual human being involved in an activity of teaching music or a software agent capable of teaching music.
An actual human being involved in an arragnement of a music piece.
A theater specifically built for opera and classical performances. It includes a stage, orchestra pit, and elaborate seating areas. Known for rich acoustics and dramatic productions.
A part of a musical event (e.g., the period in which a given musical piece has been played)

comment.en:
A music lesson event.
        Takes as agents the music teacher and music learner, as well as  teachers group and learners groups.
A service used by a musician (e.g., social networks, music editing software, digital audio workstations, music streaming services, or collaborative music making online platforms)
A group of teachers (e.g., involved in a music lesson).

comment.undefined: A software agent capable of performing activities of live sound engineering.
A sound engineer.
A private space where musicians practice individually or in groups. Often soundproof and equipped with basic instruments or gear. Typically used to prepare for performances or recordings.
An actual human being involved in an activity of learning music or a software agent capable of learning music.
The act of a given musician of participating in a musical event
An actual human being involved in an activity of teaching music.
A software agent capable of teaching music.

A large open-air or domed venue typically used for sports and major events. It can host tens of thousands of people for large-scale concerts.
Typically used for high-profile tours and festivals with massive production.

comment.en: An actual human being involved in a musical activity (e.g., composition, performance) or a software agent capable of performing a musical activity

comment.undefined: An event conducted by a unique individual. For example, a guitar recital performed by a unique classical guitar player.
A music composition event. The composition activity may be conducted by an individual or a group.
A software agent capable of directing a group of musicians, such as an orchestra director.
A public green space often used for outdoor music events and festivals. It provides a relaxed, natural setting for casual or community concerts. Usually accommodates open-air stages and large crowds.
An software agent capable of composing music.
A controlled environment for recording, mixing, and producing music. Equipped with microphones, soundboards, and editing software. Used by artists, bands, sound engineers, and producers.
An actual human sound engineer involved in sound engineering activities (e.g., mixing) during live music events (e.g., performances).

comment.en: A group of music learners (e.g., involved in a music lesson).
A group of composers (e.g., involved in a collaborative music composition activity)

comment.undefined: An event conducted by more than one individual. For instance, a concert performed by an orchestra.
A group of performers (e.g., involved in a collaborative music performance activity)
An educational institution focused on teaching music. Offers lessons, for instance, in instruments, voice, theory, and composition. It can range from local schools to prestigious conservatories.
An outdoor area used for concerts, festivals, or music gatherings. Examples include parks, fields, or city squares. Often used for large, casual, or seasonal events.

comment.en: A software application specific to the musical domain.

comment.undefined: A software agent capable of making an arragnement of a music piece.
A software agent.
A small, intimate venue dedicated to live jazz music. It often serves food and drinks, creating a relaxed atmosphere. Ideal for close interaction between performers and audience.
A software agent capable of learning music.
A group of musicians who perform a musical activity together.
An event in which an individual learns music theory or practice by himself/herself.
An actual human being involved in the direction of a group of musicians, such as an orchestra director.

A large indoor venue designed for live music performances, especially classical music. It typically features excellent acoustics and tiered seating.
Typically used by orchestras, choirs, and soloists.
A studio producer.
A software agent capable of performing.
An actual human being involved in a music composition process.
An actual human being involved in an activity of learning music.
A music performance event, such as a live concert.
The home of a musician, where s/he can perform musical activities.

An orchestra is a large group of instrumentalists who play together to perform complex music, organized into sections and with a precise structure. It typically includes strings, woodwinds, brass, and percussion sections. Orchestras perform classical music and other musical genres. They are usually led by a conductor who directs the performance.

comment.en: A musical event related to a musical activity, such as a performance, lesson, rehearsal. A musical event is composed by different musical sessions.

An event where a musician plays for fun an instrument, alone or in group.
        Takes as agent the performer.

comment.undefined: Relates a MusicianParticipation ot a musical work, such that a musician played a given musical work during a musical activity.
Relates a music teacher to a music learner, such that the teacher is the mentor of the learner.
The act of a virtual musician to recongize a given emotion while taking part in a musical event.
Relates a MusicianParticipation ot a musical work, such that a musician taught a given musical work during a musical activity.
A Performance that is part of a Festival. For example, the concert of Jimi Hendrix at Woodstock is part of such festival. Note that a Performance can be part of a Festival and also of a Tour.

comment.en: A property relating a genre as a subgenre of another. E.g., Bebop or Swing are sub-genres of the Jazz genre.

comment.undefined: A Festival that includes a Performance. For example, the 1969 edition of the Woodstock festival included a performance of Jimi Hendrix.
The act of a virtual musician to display a given emotion while taking part in a musical event.
An application runnin on a smart musical instrument has a software agent capable of performing a musical activity.
A MusicalEvent that includes a MusicalSession. For example, a lesson includes a teoretical session and a practical one.
A musical instrument (including smart instruments) is recommended to human musician.
A musician who plays a musical instrument.
This property models whether ther act of a musician of participating to an event is synchronous or asynchronous.
Relates a music learner to a music teacher, such that the learner is the pupil of the teacher.
This property models whether ther act of a musician of participating to an event is situated (i.e., in presence) or dispalced (i.e., remote).
Relates a MusicianParticipation ot a smart musical instrument, such that a musician played a given smart musical instrument during a musical activity.
Relates a MusicianParticipation to a human musician.

A Performance that is part of a Tour. For example, the concert in New York of the Dream Theater is part of the US tour of the band. Note that a Performance can be part of a Tour and also of a Festival.
Relates a music teacher to the venue where he/she conducts the teaching activity.
Indicates wether a person has a disability or not.
The act of a human musician of being interested in a given musical event.

comment.en: Property that models the fact that a human musician utilizes some kind of musical services.

comment.undefined: Relates a musical event to a group of musicians.
Relates an agent to a thing, such that the thing is recommended to the agent.
The act of a virtual musician to display a given mood while taking part in a musical event.

comment.en: This property is used to describe events that involve only one agent.
The expertise level of a musician (three constrained values: beginner, expert and intermediate).

comment.undefined: Relates a music learner to the venue where he/she conducts the learning activity.

comment.en: This property is used to describe agents able to play either one musical instrument  (single-instrumentalist) or more than one musical instrument (multi-instrumentalist)

comment.undefined: The act of a virtual musician to recongize a given mood while taking part in a musical event.
Relates a human musician to a MusicianParticipation.
A musician or a group of musicians who play a given musical genre.
Relates human beings or software agents to the performances they were involved in as live sound engineers.
A Tour that includes a Performance. For example, the 2025 US tour of the band Dream Theater includes a concert in New York.
The act of a human musician to express a given emotion while taking part in a musical event.

comment.en: The level of professionality of a musician (either amateur or professional)

comment.undefined: A MusicalSession that is part of a MusicalEvent. For example, a lesson can be composed of different parts (such as a theoretical part), each of which is a sub-musical event of the lesson.
Relates a performance to a human being or virtual agent who were involved in as live sound engineers.
A musical genre is recommended to human musician.
A MusicalEvent may be either public or private
The type of disability of a person, in terms of the following categories: auditory-, cognitively-, motor-, and visually-impaired.
A user is recommended to another user.
Relates human beings or software agents to the performances they were involved in as live sound engineers.
A musical event is recommended to human musician.
The act of a human musician to feel a given emotion while taking part in a musical event.
Relates a MusicianParticipation ot a musical work, such that a musician learnt a given musical work during a musical activity.
The act of a human musician to express a given mood while taking part in a musical event.
A musical venue is recommended to human musician.
The act of a human musician to feel a given mood while taking part in a musical event.

comment.en: This property is used to describe events that involve more than one agent.

comment.undefined: Relates a MusicianParticipation to a musical event or a part of a musical event.
A music genre is played at a music venue.
